                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-28T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 28—10:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>464. Department’s despatch October 4th.<note n="19" xml:id="d655fn19">Not
                        printed.</note> Japanese Minister has filed strong protest against Federal
                    wireless contract.</p>
                <p>Schwerin arrived here 26th. I have had two long conferences with him in which all
                    aspects of matter were discussed and I have assured him that Legation will lend
                    him all possible support.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
